Diagnosis.
This species is distinguished by the presence of one to many button-like granules on the superomarginal (
Fig. 2B,C
) and actinal plates, a duck billed (i.e. paddle-shaped) pedicellariae on the adambulacral plate (
Fig. 2E
) adjacent to furrow spines. Additionally, a bivalve pedicellariae is present on the adambulacral plate surface adjacent five to eight furrow spines (
Fig. 2E
). It possesses two to four short spines on the inferomarginal plate surface (
Fig. 2C
).
